law.text:
The Commission on the Deaf and Hard of Hearing shall provide to the General Assembly an annual report on the operation of the Telecommunications Access Program. The report shall be due on July 1 of each year, beginning July 1, 1995, and, at a minimum, provide:
The number of persons served and the number of pieces of specialized telecommunications equipment distributed;
The revenues and expenditures of the program;
Discussion of any major policy or operational issues;
Any changes the commission plans to make in the program that does not require legislative action; and
Any proposals for legislative changes in the program.
